  "prompt": "What if Obama dies before Trump is inaugurated? Would Joe Biden assume presidency or Trump take oath earlier than planned?",
  "response": "If a sitting president were to pass away between the election and the official inauguration, the line of succession follows constitutional and statutory guidelines. According to the U.S. Constitution and the Presidential Succession Act, the vice president-elect would become president if the president-elect died after the election but before inauguration.\n\nHowever, since Donald Trump won the 2016 presidential election, if President Obama had passed away before Trump's inauguration on January 20, 2017, it would not have altered the fact that Trump was elected as the next president. Joe Biden, as the vice president at the time, would have assumed the presidency only until January 20, 2017. On this date, Donald Trump would have been inaugurated as planned.\n\nIn short, Trump's scheduled inauguration would not be moved up, and he would take office on January 20, as stipulated by the Constitution.",
